datastructures.other

Interface Bag<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of element contained in a Bag.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayBag, LinkedBag

    public interface Bag<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A Bag is one of the most basic ADTs. It only supports adding elements and not accessing them individually. Bags are assumed to have infinite capacity. From the point of view of the user of this class, the order in which elements are accessed does not matter, as long as two conditions are satisfied: (1) Every iteration will exhaustively cover the elements in the bag. (2) Every element is accessed exactly once per iteration.
    Since:
    October 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
